EMER-G-MED said it dispatched multiple ambulances and response vehicles to the scene where a bakkie had rolled multiple times - the occupants had been ejected from the vehicle .Two passengers were declared dead at the scene. A third passenger who was in a very critical condition deteriorated and paramedics started CPR as part of a full advanced life support resuscitation the service said. Unfortunately he succumbed to his injuries and was declared dead on the scene. A fourth passenger sustained critical injuries and required rapid advanced life support intervention while two more patients sustained moderate injuries.EMER-G-MED said it was reported by the passengers that the driver was intoxicated - he fled the accident scene . TMG Digital